<TITLE> Muhith hints at Vested Property Act amendment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, July 17 (bdnews24.com)Finance minister A M A Muhith has hinted at amending the Vested Property Act, which minorities and rights group say infringes on . "The law framed years ago cannot be revoked right away. We may amend it, in the case the law would be made ineffective," he said at the biennial conference of Bangladesh Puja Udjapon Parishad, Sylhet district and city units at Rikabibazar on Friday. "We want proper execution of law good governance and economic freedom in the country and for that, the constitution of 1972 will have to be reinstated," he added. "We fought together for the country. We need to remove discrimination based on religions, casts to keep the society secular." bdne
